    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="437"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 War Credits/660</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Greek Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Simopoulos</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Secretary of the Treasury</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="7" xml:id="d437fn7">Handed to the Chief of the Division of
                        Near Eastern Affairs, Department of State, by the First Secretary of the
                        Greek Legation, March 29, 1934.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 995</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-29">March 29,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Under instructions from my Government, I
                    have the honor to advise the United States Government that, on account of
                    present difficulties, the Greek Government is compelled to postpone, in
                    accordance with the option granted under Clause 2 of Part 1. of the Debt and
                    Funding Agreement of May 10, 1929, between the United States and the Government
                    of Greece, the payment of Bond No. 13, <pb facs="0639" n="539" xml:id="pg_539"/>
                    dated January 1, 1928, and maturing July 1, 1934, in the amount of $150,000.00
                    on account of the funding indebtedness of the Government of Greece to the United
                    States as specified in Part 1. of such agreement.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C. <hi rend="smallcaps">Simopoulos</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
